In [12]:
import numpy as np

Q1 = np.percentile(vehicle['fuelCost08'], 25, 
                   interpolation='midpoint')
Q3 = np.percentile(vehicle['fuelCost08'], 75, 
                   interpolation='midpoint')
IQR = Q3 - Q1

print("Old Shape: ", vehicle.shape)

upper = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
lower = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR

vehicle = vehicle[(vehicle['fuelCost08'] >= lower) & (vehicle['fuelCost08'] <= upper)]

print("New Shape: ", vehicle.shape)

Old Shape:  (45961, 20)
New Shape:  (44942, 20)

3 KBQ¶

Which manufacturers excel in terms of fuel economy, annual fuel cost, and other factors, and should be stocked to improve sales efficiency?

In [27]:
# Visualization 1 - Line Chart
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.figure(figsize = (10,8))
# Calculate the average of fuel efficiency
avg_fuel_efficiency = vehicle.groupby('year')['comb08'].mean()

plt.plot(avg_fuel_efficiency.index, avg_fuel_efficiency.values, marker='o')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('The average overall fuel efficiency (MPG)')
plt.title('The average change in overall fuel efficiency over time')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.grid(True)

# plt.savefig('Line Chart.png')
plt.show()
In [30]:
# Visualization 2 - Interactive Bar Chart
year_vehicle = vehicle[(vehicle['year'] >= 2022) & (vehicle['year'] <= 2024)]

import plotly.express as px

plt.figure(figsize = (20,15))

fig = px.bar(year_vehicle, x='make', y= 'comb08', color = 'year', height = 600,
             title='Distribution of Combined Fuel Efficiency and Annual Fuel Cost (2022-2024)')
fig.update_xaxes(title='make: Manufacturers',tickangle=45)
fig.update_yaxes(title='Combined Fuel Efficiency(MPG)')
# fig.write_html('Interactive Bar Chart.html')
fig.show()
